  "chapter": {
    "number": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Judah’s Rebellion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is the vision concerning Judah and Jerusalem that Isaiah son of Amoz saw during the reigns of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen, O heavens, and give ear, O earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the LORD has spoken:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I have raised children and brought them up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but they have rebelled against Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The ox knows its owner,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the donkey its master’s manger,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but Israel does not know;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My people do not understand.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Alas, O sinful nation,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a people laden with iniquity,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a brood of evildoers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "children of depravity!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They have forsaken the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they have despised the Holy One of Israel",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and turned their backs on Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why do you want more beatings?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Why do you keep rebelling?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Your head has a massive wound,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your whole heart is afflicted.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "From the sole of your foot to the top of your head,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there is no soundness—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "only wounds and welts and festering sores",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "neither cleansed nor bandaged nor soothed with oil.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your land is desolate;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your cities are burned with fire.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Foreigners devour your fields before you—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a desolation demolished by strangers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And the Daughter of Zion is abandoned",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a shelter in a vineyard,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like a shack in a cucumber field,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a city besieged.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Unless the LORD of Hosts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "had left us a few survivors,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2511
          },
          {
            "text": "we would have become like Sodom,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we would have resembled Gomorrah.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2512
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Meaningless Offerings"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hear the word of the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you rulers of Sodom;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "listen to the instruction of our God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you people of Gomorrah!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“What good to Me is your multitude of sacrifices?”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "says the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“I am full from the burnt offerings of rams",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the fat of well-fed cattle;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I take no delight in the blood of bulls",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lambs and goats.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When you come to appear before Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who has required this of you—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "this trampling of My courts?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bring your worthless offerings no more;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your incense is detestable to Me—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "your New Moons, Sabbaths, and convocations.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I cannot endure iniquity",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in a solemn assembly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I hate your New Moons",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your appointed feasts.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They have become a burden to Me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I am weary of bearing them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When you spread out your hands in prayer,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will hide My eyes from you;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even though you multiply your prayers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will not listen.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Your hands are covered with blood.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wash and cleanse yourselves.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Remove your evil deeds from My sight.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Stop doing evil!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Learn to do right;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "seek justice and correct the oppressor.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2513
          },
          {
            "text": "Defend the fatherless",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and plead the case of the widow.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Come now, let us reason together,”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "says the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“Though your sins are like scarlet,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will be as white as snow;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "though they are as red as crimson,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will become like wool.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If you are willing and obedient,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will eat the best of the land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But if you resist and rebel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will be devoured by the sword.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "For the mouth of the LORD has spoken."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Corruption of Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "See how the faithful city has become a harlot!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "She once was full of justice;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "righteousness resided within her,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but now only murderers!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your silver has become dross;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your fine wine is diluted with water.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your rulers are rebels,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "friends of thieves.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They all love bribes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and chasing after rewards.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They do not defend the fatherless,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the plea of the widow never comes before them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore the Lord GOD of Hosts,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Mighty One of Israel, declares:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Ah, I will be relieved of My foes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and avenge Myself on My enemies.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will turn My hand against you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will thoroughly purge your dross;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will remove all your impurities.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will restore your judges as at first,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your counselors as at the beginning.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "After that you will be called the City of Righteousness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Faithful City.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Zion will be redeemed with justice,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "her repentant ones with righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But rebels and sinners will together be shattered,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and those who forsake the LORD will perish.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely you will be ashamed of the sacred oaks",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in which you have delighted;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you will be embarrassed by the gardens",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that you have chosen.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For you will become like an oak whose leaves are withered,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a garden without water.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The strong man will become tinder",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his work will be a spark;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "both will burn together,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with no one to quench the flames.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
